</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and so (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>)&nbsp;is a (local) maximum (point)<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15123271","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.1fi","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find an expression for d2ydx2 and hence determine whether each point is a local maximum or a local minimum.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}